    series: "Blast Chillers & Blast Freezers",
    models: "TBC-5, TBC-10, TBC-20, TBC-30 · TBF-5, TBF-10, TBF-20",
    description: "Traulsen blast chillers are used in LA's most demanding production kitchen environments — catering companies, hotel central kitchens, culinary school programs, and institutional food service. A blast chiller drops hot food from 140°F to 40°F within 2 hours — a HACCP requirement for large-volume food production. When a blast chiller fails, the entire production schedule stops. The Traulsen blast chiller uses a high-capacity refrigeration circuit with a more powerful compressor and fan array than a standard reach-in. Fan motor failure is the most common call — the high-speed fans in blast chillers wear significantly faster than standard reach-in fans.",
    failures: [
      "Fan motor failure — high-speed blast cycle motors have shorter lifespan than standard reach-in fans",
      "Control board failure — blast chiller control architecture is more complex than reach-in",
      "Refrigerant undercharge — blast performance drops before temperature-holding performance",
