  {
    series: "Undercounter & Spec-Grade Units",
    models: "TUC-27-D-2 · TUC-48-D-2 · TS-Series spec-grade",
    description: "Traulsen undercounter refrigerators are found in hospital nursing stations, hotel room service staging areas, and culinary school lab stations throughout SoCal. These units are specified by facility managers rather than restaurant operators, and they're often in service for 15–20 years — Traulsen's build quality supports extended service lives. The most common failure on long-service undercounters is the INTELA-TRAUL control board, which becomes unavailable from Traulsen's parts network after a certain production vintage. When original boards are no longer available, compatible aftermarket boards can be configured — but this requires knowledge of the INTELA-TRAUL wiring architecture.",
    failures: [
      "INTELA-TRAUL board discontinuation — boards for older units no longer in Traulsen parts network",
