const faqItems = [
  {
    q: "Do you service all Traulsen models including blast chillers?",
    a: `Yes — the full Traulsen commercial line: G series reach-in refrigerators and freezers, RHT/RLT half-door units, blast chillers (TBC series), blast freezers (TBF series), undercounter units, and TS spec-grade equipment. We are also equipped for INTELA-TRAUL control system diagnosis and board replacement. Call ${phone}.`
  },
  {
    q: "My Traulsen INTELA-TRAUL display is flashing and showing alarm codes — what's wrong?",
    a: "INTELA-TRAUL alarm codes on Traulsen units most commonly indicate one of three issues: a temperature probe failure (the probe drifts or reads open-circuit, triggering a false high-temperature alarm), a door-ajar condition (the door switch is stuck or the gasket is not sealing, causing a continuous door alarm), or a control board failure (the board itself has failed, causing display irregularities and alarm states that don't clear when reset). We diagnose INTELA-TRAUL systems on-site — don't simply power-cycle the unit repeatedly, as this can stress the compressor."
  },
  {
    q: "Is it worth repairing a Traulsen unit that's 10-12 years old?",
    a: "Almost always yes. Traulsen units are engineered for 15–20 year service lives with proper maintenance. A 12-year-old G-series reach-in with a failing INTELA-TRAUL board or a worn door gasket is not a unit at end-of-life — it's a unit with a specific component failure on a mechanically sound platform. Replacement cost for a new G24000R two-door reach-in is $4,500–$6,000. Board replacement: $400–$700. Gasket replacement: $150–$250. The economics strongly favor repair at virtually any point in Traulsen's service life."
  },
