        <div class="badge-inner">
          <div class="badge-brand">TRAULSEN</div>
          <div class="badge-line">ITW Food Equipment Group</div>
          <div class="badge-specs">
            <span>G Series Reach-Ins</span>
            <span>RHT Half-Door</span>
            <span>Blast Chillers</span>
            <span>INTELA-TRAUL</span>
            <span>Hotel &amp; Healthcare</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="trust-bar">
    <div class="container trust-bar-inner">
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="ti-icon">🏨</span><span>Hotel &amp; Healthcare Specialists</span></div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="ti-icon">⚡</span><span>Same-Day Emergency Response</span></div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="ti-icon">🖥️</span><span>INTELA-TRAUL Control Experts</span></div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="ti-icon">🔬</span><span>EPA 608 Certified</span></div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="ti-icon">📋</span><span>PM Contracts Available</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="intro-section container">
    <div class="intro-content">
      <h2>Traulsen Repair in Southern California — The Institutional Standard</h2>

      <p>Traulsen occupies a specific tier in commercial refrigeration — above mass-market restaurant equipment, aligned with the most demanding professional kitchen environments. When Gordon Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares kitchens get upgraded, they get Traulsen. When Cedars-Sinai or UCLA Medical Center specs a cafeteria reach-in, it's often Traulsen. When the Beverly Hills Hotel or the Biltmore needs kitchen refrigeration that will perform reliably through 200+ covers per night, they specify Traulsen. This is not coincidental — Traulsen's engineering standards, build quality, and control system sophistication are calibrated for institutional and fine dining demands.</p>

      <p>The INTELA-TRAUL microprocessor control system is the feature that most distinguishes Traulsen from True or Hoshizaki reach-ins. INTELA-TRAUL provides continuous temperature logging, configurable high and low temperature alarms, door-ajar alarms with adjustable time delays, and remote monitoring capability in current production units. When INTELA-TRAUL works, it's an invaluable food safety tool. When it fails — and board failures are one of the top three Traulsen service calls we make in SoCal — diagnosing and resolving the issue requires knowledge of the INTELA-TRAUL architecture, not just generic thermostat replacement.</p>

      <p>We service Traulsen commercial equipment throughout LA, Orange County, Ventura, and the Inland Empire. Same-day response for emergency failures. PM contracts for hotel and healthcare operators running multiple Traulsen units. EPA 608 certified. $120 commercial diagnostic applied to the repair. Call {phone}.</p>
    </div>

